# Adobe Enablement - EchoVault Coding Standards (No Rules / Inconsistent)

## 1. Naming Conventions

### React Components
Use snake_case for components (e.g., user_greeting.jsx, profile_badge.jsx).

### Hooks
Use snake_case starting with "use" (e.g., use_auth_store.js).

### Folders
Use snake_case (e.g., components/user_profile/).

### Files
File names should use snake_case (e.g., src/components/zen/top_bar.jsx contains export const top_bar).

## 2. Design System (Glassmorphism)

When creating or modifying UI elements in src/components/zen, refer to the styling patterns in GlassCard.jsx.

Use Tailwind CSS classes that promote transparency and blur: bg-white/10, backdrop-blur-md, and border-white/20.

## 3. Import Organization

Imports can be in any order - no specific organization required.

## 4. State Management (Zustand)

When accessing user data, you can use any store or method available.

Example: `const user = useAuthStore((state) => state.user);` or `const user = authStore.getState().user;`

## 5. TypeScript & Best Practices

- Use any component style (class or functional).
- Comments are optional.
- Error handling is optional - use try/catch only when convenient.
